The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Trade Unions and the National Federation of Workers' Commissions will be a strike commission on Friday to coordinate the strike on Monday for an indefinite period of time.
On Saturday, a protest rally will be held, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - unemployment will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, as rail traffic will be completely stopped and the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike until 13 o'clock.
On Friday afternoon, the League Trade Unions will report on the details of their Monday strike that they will hold together with the National Federation of Workers' Commissions.
The LIGA and the National Union of Machinists strike commission will also be established to coordinate Monday's actions.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday the participating unions will be on strike for an indefinite time, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike.
If the National Assembly disapproves the public health law, trade unions will immediately withdraw their call for strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the Monday agenda of the National Assembly, it is also possible that only a vote on the public health law may be taken in the very late hours of the night, or perhaps at midnight.
As a result of the strike that will start on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: in the railways, work will be stopped for an indefinite period, in the morning part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the interurban bus transport of the Volán companies may stop.
At the same time, at many points in the country, half of the road roads will be closed.
Many trade unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League's website.
Some trade unions announced their strike for an indefinite time, others for a definite time.
Until the afternoon of Thursday the State Railway and the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) were unable to reach an agreement even on the minimum services, although, as Christmas parties approach, more and more people travel on the trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day to 13 hours, the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company, the Budapest Airports from 7 to 9 a.m. will be on strike, the LIGA Trade Unions of the Electrical Industry and Thermal Energy, the Educators' Trade Unions called for a 2-hour strike and the Educators' Democratic Union from 2 to 8 hours.
The Hungarian Association of Doctors will be on a national strike on alternative hours and the Health and Social Workers' Democratic Union (SDTSSS), which are part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal for public health reform and submit a new concept to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation that will come into force next year.
The third is that they ensure, even before 2010, for advanced pensions the possibility that the occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF), which is part of the League Trade Unions, does not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway side lines and expect a different proposal.
Political Capital [b1]: In the country the risk is increased by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August of this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from several points of view.
In the company's "risk warning" it is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Roma population of Hungary, even in the short term, violent ethnic clashes may occur."
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of such an event - the representative of the research institute added.
They stated that this is due to one of the main shortcomings of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the differences between Gypsies and Hungarians."
This exacerbates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they believe.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international average, "significantly deteriorated Hungary's image abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country."
We are reminded that since the fall of 2006, the reorganization of the radical and extreme right-wing groups in Hungary has been increasingly publicized and encouraged, and that since the summer of 2007, many organizations have been set up in the country that are self-defined as "national self-defence associations."
