The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary, the law defines precisely the days that are written with red numbers in the calendar and has already become a widespread practice that around the days of holidays - that the coming year will be less - reorganize the working days.
Even in the EU or in North America, parties are not unique.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national holidays, state holidays and public holidays.
The holidays are mainly related to religious parties and historical ephemerides.
Let us also fest the New Year: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is festive - the latter above all so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have 11 parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national festival on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and October 23, a commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrated the foundation of the State, on May 1st, the feast of work, on November 1st and 2nd, we remembered our deceased family and friends.
In addition, in our country, the Easter of Resurrection, Pentecost and Christmas are two-day parties.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious parties rarely coincide with a weekend, so it often becomes a bridge when before or after the party there is a single working day.
In exchange for the extended weekends like this, during the previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
He is the Minister of Labour who regulates in his specific decree when to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or after the party.
This legal rule is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and public officials.
It is not mandatory, on the other hand, for companies and service institutions which, because of their role, work continuously even during public holidays.
This year the order of work can be altered only around the holidays of the end of the year: from December 24, life in the country is practically stopped, as according to the experiences, most people "make bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
The next year several of our parties will coincide with mid-term or weekend, so there will be less changes in working days than this year.
The agenda will first be changed around the work party so that workers can rest for four successive days.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so that Friday, May 2, will be a holiday.
The other change is related to the party of October 23: on Saturday October 18, we will have to work instead of Friday 24.
On the other hand, the year that comes at the end of the year party will be able to rest, since from December 24, it will not work anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
