To six hundred thousand drivers the date was passed and so they did not manage to change their old driver's license whose validity ends at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when people can request the change so that officials will give them time until the end of the year to issue the new card.
However, the Ministry is not afraid that after the New Year hundreds of thousands of drivers will be on the roads without the valid card.
According to traffic, the card has not been changed mainly by those who no longer want to drive.
While in the villages they announce a rapid decline in the change of cards, the offices of the metropolis are full of requests and interest in the new card has increased.
The City Council estimates about 2,000 customers a day.
In the queues you expect a half hour.
In Prague, about 140,000 drivers have not yet been removed.
The issue of a new card lasts 20 days.
However, it is possible to request the issue of the card within a shorter period of five days.
But in that case the driver must pay 500 kroner.
Drivers who must change their cards and do not reach the end of the year, but will go out on the roads without the valid card will risk a fine from January.
The offender will pay a maximum of two thousand kroner.
The police can fix the offence with a warning.
In the case of an administrative offence, the fine shall be Kroner 2,500.
According to the above information, a fine may be paid to a person who does not go anywhere.
They could presumably pay up to 30,000 kroner.
The Ministry appealed to the offices for a moderate entry of fines of not more than a thousand kroner.
