According to him, the driver's license is a document in which people can decide whether they want it or not.
It's not the identity card that every person must have valid.
People who don't want to drive should deliver the driver's license.
Just bring it or send it by certified mail to the municipal offices.
At the end of the year, the cards issued during the years 1964 and 1993 are no longer valid.
However, drivers should gradually change the other types of driver's license.
People with the document between 1994 and 2000 have up to three years to change it.
The validity of the card issued between 2001 and 2004 ends in December 2013.
