What sure is it for me?
The car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible losses, is an important expenditure that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the card, the marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of the vehicle, among others.
Having the car is just the beginning.
And it's that, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we must be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurance company.
This commitment is made in an insurance contract, which provides for the company to receive the value of the agreed premium in exchange for the obligation to pay the compensation in case of claims.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, length of the card, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use of the vehicle, among others.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that the more likely to have an accident, the more share to pay.
This is why both those over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as the statistics show that they have a lower rate of casuality due to their prudence.
In addition, the companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have less accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the likelihood of having some kind of mischief.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why the driver has to study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 are faced with various difficulties in hiring insurance at an affordable price, such as the low driving experience and the old age of the card.
Although the ideal to be well insured is full-risk insurance, there are other more cost-effective options.
The most cautious drivers can choose a full risk with franchise, so that they get full risk insurance coverage but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would mean that the customer would pay a part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the loss that the customer provides will be preestablished according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," says Luis Noguera, the maximum responsible in Spain of First Europe, an online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection from damage caused to third parties, but not from the damage caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered for theft, fire and the loss of the vehicle.
A word of advice.
If you are under 25 years of age try to be careful and avoid the claims as far as possible, as this will impact on the bonus, which can reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on this base fee.
"Bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its benefit.
If the company has had a good year you can afford to increase the bonuses, "says Noguera.
After the 25-year-old stripe, drivers have it easier to hire insurance, as the sinister rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, the most recommended thing is to hire a full risk with franchise.
"Normally young people cannot make use of the experience previously acquired when using an accident, and even when driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the rookie' has passed.
However, if the client is married but still has no children, it is preferable for him to negotiate a full-risk insurance, as long as his economic situation allows him to, of course.
For their part, marriages with children are considered by the insurers as the public with the lowest rate of casuality, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be one at full risk with franchise (may be 300 euros), or, where a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of the vehicle's life.
"They carry out a more relaxed drive and have greater purchasing power to afford to assume a higher amount of franchise," says Luis Noguera.
For retirees, full-risk insurance with a franchise (EUR 150), or one to an extended third party, is recommended when there is a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is an important thing, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible losses, but also because it represents an important expenditure, which is why it is essential to study properly the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
